text=Original by Baldas 17/02/06%0aUpdated by Gonad 17/02/06 13:00 %0a%0a* '''Protect Your Identity'''\\\%0a%0aTitles: The words IDENTITY and THEFT appear on the screen, and a hand comes in from the side and steals a couple of letters.%0a%0aWe see Man 1 standing somewhere (possibly outside). He is wearing a shirt and tie and glasses.%0a%0aUnseen announcer: "Protect yourself from identity theft!"%0a%0aMan 2 walks into view. He is dressed differently to Man 1, and isn't wearing glasses. He reaches across to Man 1 and takes his glasses and puts them on himself. There is a flash and now they have instantly swapped clothing and wigs as well. Man 2 starts walking away.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "Is this identity theft?"%0a%0aClose-up of the faces of Man 1 and Man 2 waiting keenly for the answer to this question.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "No it isn't."%0a%0aAnother flash, and Man 1 and Man 2 swap back to their original clothing/wigs/glasses.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "Identity theft is much worse than that."%0a%0aMan 1 is opening his credit card bill. There are lots of items with big figures next to them. No company names are mentioned, just things like "Betting shop £300, Off licence £100, Supermarket £200, Saucy Sues Marital Aids £350, Electrical store £1000". We hear him saying things like "What on earth?" and "I didn't spend that!".%0a%0aHis eyes (and our camera) focus on the figure at the bottom, £5000 or whatever, and we hear a "good grief" from our man.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "How did this happen?"%0a%0aWe see Man 1 standing inside his house, and our camera view pulls right back so that we see the garden and then the edge of the street, and then the wheely bin outside his house. %0a%0aCaption at bottom of screen saying "Last Week...". %0a%0aMan 2 is rummaging through the bin. He finds an old bank statement (again faked, maybe from "Bank Of Britain", but it looks real and has Man 1's name and address on it). There is an electricity bill as well, maybe from British Power. %0a%0aMan 2 runs off with them.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "With a few household bills or bank statements of yours, somebody can pretend to be you. Infact from an electronic point of view, they ARE YOU"%0a%0aMan 2 is holding the bills he stole, sitting in a darkened room, and his face morphs into that of Man 1, who starts laughing evilly. We could possibly use that Matrix style effect as part of the morph here.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "And the consequences might be more than financial".%0a%0aWe see Man 1 answering the door. A policeman comes in.%0a%0aPoliceman: "I'm arresting you on suspicion of terrorism".%0a%0aMan 1: "But I'm innocent!"%0a%0aThe policeman leads Man 1 away in handcuffs.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "Remember SITGAS. STOP IDENTITY THEFT, GET A SHREDDER."%0a%0aThe acronym is spelt down the screen in red and as the announcer says each work, the rest of the word appears next to the initial letter, in white.%0a%0aNot sure about this epilogue though:%0a%0aWe see Man 1 (in the same clothes as the first scene) in his house using a shredder. However, his tie is getting quite close to the opening in the shredder.%0a%0aAnnouncer: "But don't get your tie caught in it!"%0a%0aThe screen goes black and we hear a grinding, tearing noise and Man 1 saying, "Uh oh!" or something like that.%0a%0aThe end.\\%0a(If it is too long we can cut out the bit with the policeman)%0a%0a%0a'''Props Required:'''\\\%0a%0aplastic/paper letters to spell out title (gonad)\\%0a2 outfits and wigs (gonad)\\%0ashredder\\%0apolice uniform (gonad)\\%0afake credit card bill (gonad)\\%0afake bank statement (gonad)\\%0afake utility bill (gonad)\\%0adustbin (use binbags instead)\\%0a\\\%0a%0a'''Cast:'''\\\%0a%0aMan 1\\%0aMan 2\\%0aAnnouncer\\%0aPoliceman\\%0a\\\
